athcool: athcool (powersaving mode for AMD Athlon/Duron processors)
athcool:
athcool: Since enabling Powersaving mode, you can save power consumption,
athcool: lower CPU temperature when CPU is idle.
athcool:
athcool: Powersaving works if your kernel support ACPI (APM not work),
athcool: because athcool only set/unset "Disconnect enable when STPGNT
athcool: detected" bits in the Northbridge of Chipset. To really save
athcool: power, someone has to send the STPGNT signal when idle. This is
athcool: done by the ACPI subsystem when C2 state enterd.
athcool:
